Continuous red light: pay attention to wait
Sometimes a traffic light is not just green.
The detection loop in the road does not respond, or the sign of light is defective.
What should you do then - red?
An affected party has waited long enough at a red light, and the crossing is free, can he continue, the Stuttgart-based lawyer Ralf Becker in the magazine "Motorrad" explains.
The wait must be but 'reasonable', which could be interpreted differently from case to case.
Becker advises to endure at least five minutes, before is assumed by the traffic light malfunction.
Who continues the journey despite red light, must be however aware that he carries the full blame for an accident caused by this.
Who are tolerated less than five minutes, wait long enough under certain circumstances, warns Becker and refers to a decision of the Oberlandesgericht Hamm.
